question: What is the name of the Start-up India International Summit organised by DPIIT?
explanation:
The “Start-up India International Summit” named Prarambh is organised by Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade, Ministry of Commerce. It is a 2-day event.
The summit aims to bring some of the leading minds from around the world on one platform and deliberate about the collaboration between countries on start-up ecosystems.
